## Sidebar & Header Setup

```tsx
// Every authenticated layout — sidebar + scrollable content column
<SidebarProvider>
  <div className="flex h-svh overflow-hidden bg-tatva-surface-primary">
    <Sidebar
      menuItems={[
        { label: "Build", collapsible: true, items: [
          { label: "Agents", icon: "ai-magic", href: "/agents" },
        ]},
      ]}
      footerMenuItems={[{ label: "Settings", icon: "filter-horizontal", href: "/settings" }]}
      profile={{ name: "Ananya Iyer", onProfileClick: () => {} }}
      activePath={pathname}
    />
    <Box display="flex" direction="column" m={4} grow shrink minW="0" overflow="hidden" rounded="md" bg="surface-secondary">
      <Header type="main" left={{ title: "Page title" }} />
      <Box as="main" grow overflow="auto" p={12}>
        {children}
      </Box>
    </Box>
  </div>
</SidebarProvider>
```

- Always group `menuItems` — never flat array at the top level without a group label.
- `profile.onProfileClick` for simple navigation; `profile.actions` for a dropdown menu. Don't combine both.
- `Header` types: `main` (dashboard pages) · `panel` (sheets/modals) · `canvas` (editors, chat).

## Visual Quality

- **3 levels of weight per screen**: hero (`heading-md/lg`, large metric values) → supporting (`label-md` tone secondary, section titles) → body (`body-sm` tone secondary/tertiary). Never the same variant for a label and its value.
- **Surface depth**: shell `surface-primary` → content area `surface-secondary + shadow-tatva-l1` → inputs/rows `background-primary`. Never put everything on one flat plane.
- **Spacing rhythm**: dashboard card row `gap-tatva-6` · between sections `gap-tatva-12` · page padding `p-tatva-16`. Settings field group gap `gap-tatva-8` · between groups `gap-tatva-16`.
- **Badge color convention**: green=active/live/success · red=error/danger · yellow=warning/pending · indigo or brand=category/feature label.
- **Replicating a design**: identify grid columns → map each block to a Tatva component → match spacing rhythm → match typography weight → done.

